  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6659",
  "title": "Refinement doesn't clear if same attribute is present with 2 different filters",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nWe have a specific need where we need to have a range filter as long as some preset filters that filter by single value.\n\nSo for example: a year range filter where you can filter >= xYear, but at the same time be able to just filter by year = xYear.\n\nTo da that we are combining a range with a refinement list, but when clearing, the refinementList does not clear when using clearRefinements\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Add a filter with the range. eg: min: 2500.\n2. Filter with a preset\n3. Clear refinement\n\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/github/algolia/instantsearch/tree/templates/react-instantsearch\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nExpected Behaviour: all filters clear\nActual behaviour: only range clears\n\n### Package version\n\n\"instantsearch.js\": \"^4.78.3\"\n\"react-instantsearch\": \"^7.15.7\"\n\"react-instantsearch-nextjs\": \"^0.4.9\"\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
